(2367,'Sympathetic Vibration','Deals 2d10 damage/round to freestanding structure.','By attuning yourself to a freestanding damage per round to the target structure. (Hardness has no effect on the spells damage.) You can choose at the time of casting to limit the duration of the spell,otherwise it lasts for 1 round/level. If the spell is cast upon a target that is not freestanding the surrounding stone dissipates the effect and no damage occurs. Sympathetic vibration cannot affect creatures (including constructs). Since a structure is an unattended object, it gets no saving throw to resist the effect. Focus A tuning fork.','10 mins','Touch',1,NULL,'','to 1 rd','None*','Yes',5,6,NULL,NULL),
(2368,'Sympathy','Object or location attracts certain creatures.','You cause an object or location to emanate magical vibrations that attract either a specific kind of intelligent creature or creatures of a particular alignment, as defined by you. The particular kind of creature to be affected must be named specifically for example, red dragons, hill giants, wererats, lammasus, or vampires. A creature subtvpe (such as goblinoid) is not specific enough. Likewise, the specific alignment must be named-for example.chaotic evil.chaotic good, lawful neutral, or neutral. Creatures of the specified kind or alignment feel elated and pleased to be in the area or desire to touch or to possess the obiect.The compulsion to stay in the area or touch the object is overpowering. If the save is successful, the creature is released from the enchantment, but a subsequent save must be made 1d610 minutes later. If this save fails, the affected creature attempts to return to the area or object. Sympathy counters and dispels antipathy.Material Component 1,500 gp worth of crushed pearls and a drop of honey,','1 hr','Close',3,NULL,'','2 hr(D)','Will neg*','Yes',5,8,NULL,NULL),
